 THE Katsina State command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) has said it received 795 criminal and civil cases between January and August. Spokesman Mohammed Tukur-Abdara said in a statement on Tuesday in Katsina that out of the 795 csses, 418 were criminal cases while 377 were civil in nature. He said that the criminal cases were related to theft, drug abuse and trafficking, rape, vandalism, unnatural offence and trespass.   